Photochemistry is the study of the effects of light on chemistry. The fading of
a dye is due to photochemistry, and photosynthesis is one of the most important
examples of photochemistry. The absorption of light by a molecule changes the
molecule’s chemistry by altering the molecule’s geometry or rearranging its
electron density. In this experiment we will probe the photoacidity of
2-naphthol.

